<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="V" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Valentinus" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Valentinus,</orth> another form of Valentine in <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.3.67" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 3, 67</bibl> (later Ff <emph>Valentino</emph>). Some M. Edd. <emph>V.</emph> in <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.196" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 4, 196</bibl> (O. Edd. <emph>Valentine's</emph>) and <bibl n="shak. mm 4.5.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 5, 8</bibl> (O. Edd. <emph>Valencius</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>